2 year.
3 B. The increase prescribed by this section shall be in addition
4 to any other compensation, increase in compensation, and fringe
5 benefits provided by the school district or state, or mandated by
6 law or collective bargaining agreement, unless the hours or duties
7 of the classroom teacher are reduced proportionately.
8 C. For purposes of this section, "classroom teacher" means a
9 teacher as defined in paragraph 1 of Section 1-116 of Title 70 of
10 the Oklahoma Statutes, except for superintendents as defined in
11 paragraph 2 of Section 1-116 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
